  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  The patient experiences pain and limitations of the great toe dorsiflexion at the
             MTP-I joint.

          -  The patient has a clinically and radiographically verified arthritis in the MTP-I
             joint indicating the need for surgical treatment.

          -  The patient reads, understands and is able to complete the study questionnaires in
             Swedish.

          -  The patient has received written and oral information regarding the study and has
             signed the informed consent form.

        Exclusion criteria:

          -  The patient has a pronounced hallux rigidus without mobility in the MTP-I joint (ROM =
             0°).

          -  The patient has previously received surgical treatment affecting the anatomy of the
             MTP-I joint.

          -  The patient has a systemic rheumatic disease, ongoing infection, hallux valgus or is
             seriously ill.
      </textblock>
